Crackclaw Point07016tildji1ehwgv1l96odc8nxrr4wxztd11662632014-11-26T20:46:51ZThe Dragon Demands5014364[[Image:Crackclaw Point.png|thumb|right|200px|A map showing the location of Crackclaw Point on the continent of Westeros.]]
'''Crackclaw Point''' is a region in [[the Crownlands]]. It is a large peninsula north-east of [[King's Landing]], on the east coast of [[Westeros]]. It extends into the [[Narrow Sea]], forming the northern shore of [[Blackwater Bay]]. [[Claw Isle]] lies just off the eastern edge of Crackclaw Point, with [[Dragonstone]] located off the south coast. The ruins known as [[the Whispers]] are located at the tip of the peninsula.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season1/#!/locations/kings-landing/ HBO viewers guide, season 1 map, King's Landing entry]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=&quot;Viewers Guide&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/kings-landing/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, King's Landing entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

[[House Brune]] is a poor vassal House from Crackclaw Point.
